{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.21",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 21 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:2",
      "text": "Hear, I beseech you, my words, and do penance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:3",
      "text": "Suffer me, and I will speak, and after, if you please, laugh at my words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:4",
      "text": "Is my debate against man, that I should not have just reason to be troubled?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:5",
      "text": "Hearken to me and be astonished, and lay your finger on your mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:6",
      "text": "As for me, when I remember, I am afraid, and trembling taketh hold on my flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:7",
      "text": "Why then do the wicked live, are they advanced, and strengthened with riches?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:8",
      "text": "Their seed continueth before them, a multitude of kinsmen, and of children's children in their sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:9",
      "text": "Their houses are secure and peaceable, and the rod of God is not upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:10",
      "text": "Their cattle have conceived, and failed not: their cow has calved, and is not deprived of her fruit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:11",
      "text": "Their little ones go out like a flock, and their children dance and play.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:12",
      "text": "They take the timbrel, and the harp, and rejoice at the sound of the organ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:13",
      "text": "They spend their days in wealth, and in a moment they go down to hell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:14",
      "text": "Who have said to God: Depart from us, we desire not the knowledge of thy ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:15",
      "text": "Who is the Almighty, that we should serve him? and what doth it profit us if we pray to him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:16",
      "text": "Yet because their good things are not in their hand, may the counsel of the wicked be far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:17",
      "text": "How often shall the lamp of the wicked be put out, and a deluge come upon them, and he shall distribute the sorrows of his wrath?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:18",
      "text": "They shall be as chaff before the face of the wind, and as ashes which the whirlwind scattereth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:19",
      "text": "God shall lay up the sorrow of the father for his children: and when he shall repay, then shall he know.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:20",
      "text": "His eyes shall see his own destruction, and he shall drink of the wrath of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:21",
      "text": "For what is it to him what befalleth his house after him: and if the number of his months be diminished by one half?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:22",
      "text": "Shall any one teach God knowledge, who judgeth those that are high?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:23",
      "text": "One man dieth strong, and hale, rich and happy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:24",
      "text": "His bowels are full of fat, and his bones are moistened with marrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:25",
      "text": "But another dieth in bitterness of soul without any riches:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:26",
      "text": "And yet they shall sleep together in the dust, and worms shall cover them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:27",
      "text": "Surely I know your thoughts, and your unjust judgments against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:28",
      "text": "For you say: Where is the house of the prince? and where are the dwelling places of the wicked?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:29",
      "text": "Ask any one of them that go by the way, and you shall perceive that he knoweth these same things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:30",
      "text": "Because the wicked man is reserved to the day of destruction, and he shall be brought to the day of wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:31",
      "text": "Who shall reprove his way to his face? and who shall repay him what he hath done?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:32",
      "text": "He shall be brought to the graves, and shall watch in the heap of the dead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:33",
      "text": "He hath been acceptable to the gravel of Cocytus, and he shall draw every man after him, and there are innumerable before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.21.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:34",
      "text": "How then do ye comfort me in vain, whereas your answer is shewn to be repugnant to truth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
